Stagg Street, north side, west from Humboldt Street.

October 25, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

1.
Humboldt Street, nolrth from No. 232 at right, just north of Stagg Street. At left on Maujer Street, is seen St. John's Evang. Lutheran Church. The demolished buildings are being replaced with Federal low rental apartments.
December 22, 1935
P.L. Sperr

2.
The same, all debris having been removed.

P.L. Sperr

3.
The same, showing partial erection of the new apartments.

September 26, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Stagg Street, near the N.W. corner of Humbolt Street. In the background, is Ten Eyck Street, north side, between Graham and Bushwick Aves; also in the background, is seen the steeple of St. John's Evang. Luth. Church.
